h3cIPSecMonitor.name: h3cIPSecMonitor
h3cIPSecMonitor.contactinfo: Huawei 3Com Technologies Co., Ltd. Shang-Di Information Industry Base, Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.huawei-3com.com ZIP: 100085
h3cIPSecMonitor.description: The MIB is designed to get statistic information of IPSec tunnels. With this MIB, we can get information of a certain tunnel or all tunnels.

H3cDiffHellmanGrp.name: H3cDiffHellmanGrp
H3cDiffHellmanGrp.description: The Diffie Hellman Group used in the IKE and IPSec negotiations. invalidGroup(2147483647) is defined as invalid value.

H3cEncapMode.name: H3cEncapMode
H3cEncapMode.description: The encapsulation mode used by an IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel. invalidMode(2147483647) is defined as invalid value.

H3cEncryptAlgo.name: H3cEncryptAlgo
H3cEncryptAlgo.description: The encryption algorithm used in the IKE and IPSec negotiations. invalidAlg(2147483647) is defined as invalid value.

H3cAuthAlgo.name: H3cAuthAlgo
H3cAuthAlgo.description: The authentication algorithm used in the IKE negotiations. invalidAlg(2147483647) is defined as invalid value.

H3cTrapStatus.name: H3cTrapStatus
H3cTrapStatus.description: The switch which determines whether send a trap or not.

H3cTrafficType.name: H3cTrafficType
H3cTrafficType.description: The type of the data flow.

H3cIPSecNegoType.name: H3cIPSecNegoType
H3cIPSecNegoType.description: The type of key used by an IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel. invalidType(2147483647) is defined as invalid value.

h3cIPSecTunnelTable.name: h3cIPSecTunnelTable
h3cIPSecTunnelTable.description: The IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel Table. There is one entry in this table for each active IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunIfIndex.name: h3cIPSecTunIfIndex
h3cIPSecTunIfIndex.description: The interface index( the ifIndex of ifTable ).

h3cIPSecTunEntryIndex.name: h3cIPSecTunEntryIndex
h3cIPSecTunEntryIndex.description: The index of IPSec policy applied in the interface.

h3cIPSecTunIndex.name: h3cIPSecTunIndex
h3cIPSecTunIndex.description: The index of IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel Table. The value of the index is a number which begins at one and is incremented with each tunnel that is created. The value of this object will wrap at 2,147,483,647.

h3cIPSecTunIKETunnelIndex.name: h3cIPSecTunIKETunnelIndex
h3cIPSecTunIKETunnelIndex.description: The index of the associated IPSec Phase-1 IKE Tunnel (IKETunIndex in the IKETunnelTable). 2147483647 is defined as invalid value.

h3cIPSecTunLocalAddr.name: h3cIPSecTunLocalAddr
h3cIPSecTunLocalAddr.description: The IP address of the local peer for the IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel. 0.0.0.0 is defined as invalid value.

h3cIPSecTunRemoteAddr.name: h3cIPSecTunRemoteAddr
h3cIPSecTunRemoteAddr.description: The IP address of the remote peer for the IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel. 0.0.0.0 is defined as invalid value.

h3cIPSecTunKeyType.name: h3cIPSecTunKeyType
h3cIPSecTunKeyType.description: The key negotiate mode used by the IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunEncapMode.name: h3cIPSecTunEncapMode
h3cIPSecTunEncapMode.description: The encapsulation mode used by the IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunInitiator.name: h3cIPSecTunInitiator
h3cIPSecTunInitiator.description: The initiator of this IPSec tunnel. Value none is used for manual IPsec tunnel, for there is no initiator or responder in this method.

h3cIPSecTunLifeSize.name: h3cIPSecTunLifeSize
h3cIPSecTunLifeSize.description: The negotiated LifeSize of the IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel in kilobytes. 0 is defined as invalid value.

h3cIPSecTunLifeTime.name: h3cIPSecTunLifeTime
h3cIPSecTunLifeTime.description: The negotiated LifeTime of the IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel in seconds. 2147483647 is defined as invalid value.

h3cIPSecTunRemainTime.name: h3cIPSecTunRemainTime
h3cIPSecTunRemainTime.description: The remain time of SA in seconds. 2147483647 is defined as invalid value.

h3cIPSecTunActiveTime.name: h3cIPSecTunActiveTime
h3cIPSecTunActiveTime.description: The duration the IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel has been active in hundredths of seconds. 2147483647 is defined as invalid value.

h3cIPSecTunRemainSize.name: h3cIPSecTunRemainSize
h3cIPSecTunRemainSize.description: The remain LifeSize of SA in kilobytes. 0 is defined as invalid value.

h3cIPSecTunTotalRefreshes.name: h3cIPSecTunTotalRefreshes
h3cIPSecTunTotalRefreshes.description: The total number of security association refreshing performed.

h3cIPSecTunCurrentSaInstances.name: h3cIPSecTunCurrentSaInstances
h3cIPSecTunCurrentSaInstances.description: The number of security associations which are currently active or expiring.

h3cIPSecTunInSaEncryptAlgo.name: h3cIPSecTunInSaEncryptAlgo
h3cIPSecTunInSaEncryptAlgo.description: The encryption algorithm used by the inbound security association of the IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunInSaAhAuthAlgo.name: h3cIPSecTunInSaAhAuthAlgo
h3cIPSecTunInSaAhAuthAlgo.description: The authentication algorithm used by the inbound authentication header (AH) security association of the IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunInSaEspAuthAlgo.name: h3cIPSecTunInSaEspAuthAlgo
h3cIPSecTunInSaEspAuthAlgo.description: The authentication algorithm used by the inbound encapsulation security protocol(ESP) security association of the IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunDiffHellmanGrp.name: h3cIPSecTunDiffHellmanGrp
h3cIPSecTunDiffHellmanGrp.description: The Diffie Hellman Group used by the security association of the IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunOutSaEncryptAlgo.name: h3cIPSecTunOutSaEncryptAlgo
h3cIPSecTunOutSaEncryptAlgo.description: The encryption algorithm used by the outbound security association of the IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunOutSaAhAuthAlgo.name: h3cIPSecTunOutSaAhAuthAlgo
h3cIPSecTunOutSaAhAuthAlgo.description: The authentication algorithm used by the outbound authentication header (AH) security association of the IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunOutSaEspAuthAlgo.name: h3cIPSecTunOutSaEspAuthAlgo
h3cIPSecTunOutSaEspAuthAlgo.description: The authentication algorithm used by the outbound encapsulation security protocol(ESP) security association of the IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunPolicyName.name: h3cIPSecTunPolicyName
h3cIPSecTunPolicyName.description: The policy name used by this IPSec tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunPolicyNum.name: h3cIPSecTunPolicyNum
h3cIPSecTunPolicyNum.description: The sequence number of policy used by this IPSec tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunStatus.name: h3cIPSecTunStatus
h3cIPSecTunStatus.description: The status of the IPSec Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunnelStatTable.name: h3cIPSecTunnelStatTable
h3cIPSecTunnelStatTable.description: The IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel Statistics Table.

h3cIPSecTunInOctets.name: h3cIPSecTunInOctets
h3cIPSecTunInOctets.description: The total number of octets received by this IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated BEFORE determining whether or not the packet should be decompressed.

h3cIPSecTunInDecompOctets.name: h3cIPSecTunInDecompOctets
h3cIPSecTunInDecompOctets.description: The total number of decompressed octets received by this IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated AFTER the packet is decompressed.

h3cIPSecTunInPkts.name: h3cIPSecTunInPkts
h3cIPSecTunInPkts.description: The total number of packets received by this IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunInDropPkts.name: h3cIPSecTunInDropPkts
h3cIPSecTunInDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped during receiving process by this IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunInReplayDropPkts.name: h3cIPSecTunInReplayDropPkts
h3cIPSecTunInReplayDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped during receiving process due to Anti-Replay process by this IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunInAuthFails.name: h3cIPSecTunInAuthFails
h3cIPSecTunInAuthFails.description: The total number of inbound authentication's which ended in failure by this IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunInDecryptFails.name: h3cIPSecTunInDecryptFails
h3cIPSecTunInDecryptFails.description: The total number of inbound decryption's which ended in failure by this IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunOutOctets.name: h3cIPSecTunOutOctets
h3cIPSecTunOutOctets.description: The total number of octets sent by this IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel. This value is accumulated AFTER determining whether or not the packet should be compressed.

h3cIPSecTunOutUncompOctets.name: h3cIPSecTunOutUncompOctets
h3cIPSecTunOutUncompOctets.description: The total number of uncompressed octets sent by this IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.This value is accumulated BEFORE the packet is compressed.

h3cIPSecTunOutPkts.name: h3cIPSecTunOutPkts
h3cIPSecTunOutPkts.description: The total number of packets sent by this IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunOutDropPkts.name: h3cIPSecTunOutDropPkts
h3cIPSecTunOutDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped during sending process by this IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunOutEncryptFails.name: h3cIPSecTunOutEncryptFails
h3cIPSecTunOutEncryptFails.description: The total number of outbound encryption's which ended in failure by this IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunNoMemoryDropPkts.name: h3cIPSecTunNoMemoryDropPkts
h3cIPSecTunNoMemoryDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped due to no enough memory by this IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunQueueFullDropPkts.name: h3cIPSecTunQueueFullDropPkts
h3cIPSecTunQueueFullDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped due to queue full by this IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunInvalidLenDropPkts.name: h3cIPSecTunInvalidLenDropPkts
h3cIPSecTunInvalidLenDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped due to invalid length packet by this IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunTooLongDropPkts.name: h3cIPSecTunTooLongDropPkts
h3cIPSecTunTooLongDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped due to too long packet by this IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecTunInvalidSaDropPkts.name: h3cIPSecTunInvalidSaDropPkts
h3cIPSecTunInvalidSaDropPkts.description: The total number of packets dropped due to invalid SA by this IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecSaTable.name: h3cIPSecSaTable
h3cIPSecSaTable.description: The IPSec Phase-2 Security Protection Index Table. This table contains an entry for each active and expiring security association.

h3cIPSecSaIndex.name: h3cIPSecSaIndex
h3cIPSecSaIndex.description: The number of the Sa associated with the Phase-2 Tunnel Table. The value of this index is a number which begins at one and is incremented with each Sa associated with an IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel. The value of this object will wrap at 2,147,483,647.

h3cIPSecSaProtocol.name: h3cIPSecSaProtocol
h3cIPSecSaProtocol.description: The security protocol of the SA.

h3cIPSecSaEncryptAlgo.name: h3cIPSecSaEncryptAlgo
h3cIPSecSaEncryptAlgo.description: The encryption algorithm used by the security association of the IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel.

h3cIPSecSaAuthAlgo.name: h3cIPSecSaAuthAlgo
h3cIPSecSaAuthAlgo.description: The authentication algorithm used by the SA.

h3cIPSecTrafficTable.name: h3cIPSecTrafficTable
h3cIPSecTrafficTable.description: The IPSec Phase-2 Tunnel Traffic Table.

h3cIPSecTrafficLocalType.name: h3cIPSecTrafficLocalType
h3cIPSecTrafficLocalType.description: The type of local peer. Possible values are: a single IP address, or an IP address range, or an IP subnet.

h3cIPSecTrafficLocalAddr1.name: h3cIPSecTrafficLocalAddr1
h3cIPSecTrafficLocalAddr1.description: The first specification of local peer's IP address. If the local peer type is single IP address, then this is the value of the IP address. If the local peer type is IP subnet, then this is the value of the subnet. If the local peer type is IP address range, then this is the value of beginning IP address of the range.

h3cIPSecTrafficLocalAddr2.name: h3cIPSecTrafficLocalAddr2
h3cIPSecTrafficLocalAddr2.description: The second specification of local peer's IP address. If the local peer type is single IP address, then this is the value of the IP address. If the local peer type is IP subnet, then this is the value of the subnet mask. If the local peer type is IP address range, then this is the value of ending IP address of the range.

h3cIPSecTrafficLocalProtocol.name: h3cIPSecTrafficLocalProtocol
h3cIPSecTrafficLocalProtocol.description: The protocol number of the local peer's traffic.

h3cIPSecTrafficLocalPort.name: h3cIPSecTrafficLocalPort
h3cIPSecTrafficLocalPort.description: The port number of the local peer's traffic.

h3cIPSecTrafficRemoteType.name: h3cIPSecTrafficRemoteType
h3cIPSecTrafficRemoteType.description: The type of remote peer. Possible values are: a single IP address, or an IP address range, or an IP subnet.

h3cIPSecTrafficRemoteAddr1.name: h3cIPSecTrafficRemoteAddr1
h3cIPSecTrafficRemoteAddr1.description: The first specification of remote peer's IP address. If the remote peer type is single IP address, then this is the value of the IP address. If the remote peer type is IP subnet, then this is the value of the subnet. If the remote peer type is IP address range, then this is the value of beginning IP address of the range.

h3cIPSecTrafficRemoteAddr2.name: h3cIPSecTrafficRemoteAddr2
h3cIPSecTrafficRemoteAddr2.description: Single IP address, then this is the value of the IP address. If the remote peer type is IP subnet, then this is the value of the subnet mask. If the remote peer type is IP address range, then this is the value of ending IP address of the range.

h3cIPSecTrafficRemoteProtocol.name: h3cIPSecTrafficRemoteProtocol
h3cIPSecTrafficRemoteProtocol.description: The protocol number of the remote peer's traffic.

h3cIPSecTrafficRemotePort.name: h3cIPSecTrafficRemotePort
h3cIPSecTrafficRemotePort.description: The port number of the remote peer's traffic.

h3cIPSecGlobalActiveTunnels.name: h3cIPSecGlobalActiveTunnels
h3cIPSecGlobalActiveTunnels.description: The total number of currently active IPSec Phase-2 Tunnels.

h3cIPSecGlobalInOctets.description: The total number of octets received by all current and previous IPSec Phase-2 Tunnels. This value is accumulated BEFORE determining whether or not the packet should be decompressed.

h3cIPSecGlobalInDecompOctets.description: The total number of decompressed octets received by all current and previous IPSec Phase-2 Tunnels. This value is accumulated AFTER the packet is decompressed.

h3cIPSecGlobalInPkts.name: h3cIPSecGlobalInPkts
h3cIPSecGlobalInPkts.description: The total number of packets received by all current and previous IPSec Phase-2 Tunnels.

h3cIPSecGlobalOutOctets.description: The total number of octets sent by all current and previous IPSec Phase-2 Tunnels. This value is accumulated AFTER determining whether or not the packet should be compressed.

h3cIPSecGlobalOutUncompOctets.description: The total number of uncompressed octets sent by all current and previous IPSec Phase-2 Tunnels. This value is accumulated BEFORE the packet is compressed.

h3cIPSecGlobalOutPkts.name: h3cIPSecGlobalOutPkts
h3cIPSecGlobalOutPkts.description: The total number of packets sent by all current and previous IPSec Phase-2 Tunnels.

h3cIPSecGlobalNoMemoryDropPkts.name: h3cIPSecGlobalNoMemoryDropPkts
